    <subfield code="y">00002 The observer's worldline $z=0$ and the connecting geodesic $P_0 P_1$ in the boundary-value problem for wave-synchronous coordinates. $P_0 P_1$ lies in the plane $u = {\mathrm{const}}$ which coincides with one of the surfaces of constant phase of the gravitational wave. Negative values of parameter $\sigma$ correspond to the second connecting geodesic $P_0 P_2$, where $P_2 =\{\tau, -x, -y, z \}$. (In $z\tau$ plane $P_2$ appears at the same location as $P_1$.)</subfield>
