    <subfield code="y">00000 The observer's worldline $z=0$ and the connecting geodesic $P_0 P_1$ in the boundary-value problem for Fermi normal coordinates. Negative values of parameter $\sigma$ correspond to the extension of the connecting geodesic into the past. The inverse of $P_1 = \{\tau, x, y, z\}$ is $P_2 \approx \{2s-\tau, -x, -y, -z \}$.</subfield>
  </datafield>
